resources.description:
Collects time series Physochemical In-situ parameter readings every half hour for 2016. Parameters specifically, in order, are;
- Timestamp
- Record
- Temperature_Deg C
- Specific Conductivity_ uScm
- pH
- Dissolved Oxygen_%Sat
- Dissolved Oxygen_mgl
- Turbidity_ NTU
- Chlorophylla _ugl
Yellow in colour, this is a floating 0.9 m diameter Buoy anchored within the tidal zone at the Ferry Crossing approximately 16 klm from the mouth of Baffle Creek, Lat -24.50861 Long 151.9279 Datum GDA. Water column depth at this position is approximaterly 3.0 meters. Readings are taken from submersed YSI 6 series instrument Model 6600 at 0.2m below water surface.See YSi website for instrument accuracy, method of operation etc.
resources.name: Baffle Creek 2016 (near real-time)

resources.description: This theme depicts the extent of identified coal resource estimates in Queensland (nominally of either Measured and/or Indicted confidence categories) as presented in the publication 'Queensland Coals - Physical and Chemical Properties Colliery and Company Information' - 14th Edition, (Mutton 2003).The estimates tabulated therein (Appendix A) were compiled from a variety of sources and cover a range timeframes as detailed in pages 12 and 13 of that document, falling into two broad groups comprising:-historical ('legacy') estimates - nominally prepared using the applicable Australian and/or Departmental estimation/reporting codes* of the time and-those which nominally were prepared in accordance with the intent of the 1999 edition of the 'Australasian Code for Reporting of Mineral Resources and Ore Reserves' - a Code prepared by the Joint Ore Reserve Committee of the Australian Institute of Mining and Metallurgy - commonly referred to as the' JORC Code'.The current (2012) edition of the JORC Code is available from &amp=&lt=&a rel="jorc" href="http://www.jorc.org/"&amp=&gt=&http://www.jorc.org/=&amp=&lt=&/a=&amp=&gt=&.Note that since of the compilation reported by Mutton (2003), some new estimates may have been added to the layer and a few may have been renamed.*Refers to a variety of historical documents used by the Queensland coal industry preceding the introduction of the JORC Code(s) that includes the:-'Code for Reporting of Identified Coal Resources and Reserves' compiled by Galligan (A.G.) and Mengel (D.C), Queensland Government Mining Journal, (May 1986) Volume 87, 201-203. And- 'Parameters for the Reporting and Calculation of Coal Reserves', Department of Mines, November 1977. -'Parameters for the Calculation and Reporting of Coal Reserves, Queensland', Department of Mines, Queensland Government Mining Journal, September 1968 - Volume 68, No 803, pp 400-402.

resources.description: The Digital Cadastre DataBase (DCDB) is the spatial representation of the property boundaries in Queensland and their related property descriptions. It is a fundamental reference layer for spatial information systems in Queensland. This dataset is updated nightly.This dataset allows you to extract your area of interest using the 'clip, zip and ship' functionality. You can select areas by local government area, city or suburb (locality) or freehand over small areas. You cannot download the entire State in one single order. The dataset, "Cadastral data weekly - whole of State Queensland" provides the whole of State in one order but in file geodatabase format only. Instructions for extracting data can be found in the help pages.
resources.name: Cadastral data - Queensland - by area of interest
resources.url: http://qldspatial.information.qld.gov.au/catalogue/custom/search.page?q="Cadastral data - Queensland - by area of interest"

resources.description: The Digital Cadastre DataBase (DCDB) is the spatial representation of the property boundaries in Queensland and their related property descriptions. It is a fundamental reference layer for spatial information systems in Queensland. The DCDB is not the point of truth for property boundaries, property descriptions, or tenure information within the Department of Natural Resources and Mines. This data is updated weekly on Sunday.This dataset is a pre-packaged zip file containing the entire State cadastre in file geodatabase format. No other format is available for this dataset. The dataset, "Cadastral data - Queensland - by area of interest", allows you to extract data via local government areas in four different formats including shapefile and tabfile.
resources.name: Cadastral data weekly - whole of State Queensland
resources.url: http://qldspatial.information.qld.gov.au/catalogue/custom/search.page?q="Cadastral data weekly - whole of State Queensland"

resources.description: This dataset represents the draft SEQ Regional Plan 2016Regional LandUse Categories, composed of three land use categories: 1) Regional Landscape and Rural Production Area 2) Urban Footprint 3) Rural Living Area The dataset is produced from the Digital Cadastral Database (DCDB) March 2014, sourced from Department of Natural Resources and Mines. This includes property parcels, road, railway and watercourse boundaries. This information has been developed through a review of the current South East Queensland Regional Plan 2009-2031 - July 2009, informed by informalgovernment and public submissions, state and local government interations, updated popualtion and dwelling projections and a preferred settlement pattern of development. Definitions: Regional Landscape and Rural Production Area : Identifies areas with values that should be generally protected from urban and rural residential development. Urban Footprint : Identifies areas to accommodate urban growth to 2041Rural Living Area : Identifies areas predominantly for continuing rural residential development. The above descriptions are general only. For further information refer to the draft SEQ Regional Plan 2016, for more detailed definitions.

resources.description:
Data detailing the number of new business registration transactions by month, vehicle make, vehicle model, service location suburb and service location postcode.
 
Note: New business registration transaction is a registration transaction where a previously unregistered vehicle or registered interstate vehicle becomes registered in Queensland.
 
Service location relates to the suburb/postcode location of where the registration transaction took place (for example, dealership, customer service centre, Queensland police station, QGAP office).
